You can get one at a photography store or you can create one on your computer. Even if your printer isn't calibrated just right, your results will still be better than without using a gray card. You can make one by:
Open up your graphic software and creating an image. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/c3\/Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/c3\/Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Fill the image with black. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e3\/Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e3\/Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Use-an-18%25-Gray-Card-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

